WEBVTT

00:01.568 --> 00:08.107
♪

00:08.109 --> 00:10.109
Hear ye! Hear ye!

00:10.111 --> 00:15.114
The ponyville foal and filly
fair is almost ready to begin!

00:15.116 --> 00:18.417
<i>(excited chatter)</i>

00:18.419 --> 00:21.220
Whee! Ha ha!

00:21.222 --> 00:22.321
<i>(ding)</i>

00:22.323 --> 00:23.322
Ha ha!

00:23.324 --> 00:24.323
Hee hee hee!

00:24.325 --> 00:25.391
<i>(giggling)</i>

00:26.359 --> 00:28.293
Just because the
attendees are young,

00:28.295 --> 00:31.630
Doesn't mean they don't deserve
my very best creative work.

00:31.632 --> 00:34.033
Why, this puppet theatre
is going to be the talk

00:34.035 --> 00:35.467
Of the foal and filly fair.

00:36.703 --> 00:38.237
How could it not be?

00:38.239 --> 00:40.406
You're the one making it.

00:40.408 --> 00:42.808
Oh, but I couldn't have
done it without the help

00:42.810 --> 00:45.811
Of one of my dearest and
most supportive friends.

00:45.813 --> 00:49.148
You are my favorite dragon.

00:49.150 --> 00:51.417
Your favorite dragon?

00:51.419 --> 00:56.655
The hours have been long, the
work taxing beyond compare,

00:56.657 --> 00:59.058
But it will all be
worth it when we hear

00:59.060 --> 01:00.459
Those three little words--

01:00.461 --> 01:03.328
<i>Gruff voice: This is awful!</i>

01:03.330 --> 01:04.496
Awful?

01:04.498 --> 01:07.166
Completely unusable.

01:07.168 --> 01:09.701
Hmmm.

01:09.703 --> 01:12.471
It doesn't travel!

01:12.473 --> 01:16.475
There's no room for my puppets!

01:16.477 --> 01:19.478
It appears I won't have a
travelling puppet theatre

01:19.480 --> 01:21.480
To use after all.

01:25.618 --> 01:28.120
I don't know what that
guy was talking about.

01:28.122 --> 01:30.456
This thing is perfect.

01:36.096 --> 01:39.765
<i>♪ my little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:39.767 --> 01:40.766
<i>♪ aaaaahhh!</i>

01:40.768 --> 01:41.800
<i>♪ (upbeat)</i>

01:41.802 --> 01:44.169
<i>♪ my little pony</i>

01:44.171 --> 01:46.338
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be ♪</i>

01:46.340 --> 01:48.273
<i>♪ my little pony</i>

01:48.275 --> 01:50.476
<i>♪ until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me ♪</i>

01:50.478 --> 01:51.477
<i>♪ big adventure</i>

01:51.479 --> 01:52.611
<i>♪ tons of fun.</i>

01:52.613 --> 01:53.745
<i>♪ a beautiful heart</i>

01:53.747 --> 01:54.847
<i>♪ faithful and strong</i>

01:54.849 --> 01:55.848
<i>♪ sharing kindness</i>

01:55.850 --> 01:57.282
<i>♪ it's an easy feat</i>

01:57.284 --> 01:58.884
<i>♪ and magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete ♪</i>

01:58.886 --> 02:01.186
<i>♪ my little ponies</i>

02:01.188 --> 02:03.722
<i>♪ do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:03.724 --> 02:07.893
♪

02:12.565 --> 02:15.868
<i>Rarity: This is terrible.</i>
<i>Simply terrible!</i>

02:15.870 --> 02:17.870
<i>(sobbing)</i>

02:17.872 --> 02:20.772
So that puppeteer didn't like
your exquisitely crafted,

02:20.774 --> 02:22.774
Best puppet theatre in the
history of puppet theatres

02:25.411 --> 02:26.678
You can just contribute
something else

02:26.680 --> 02:28.413
To the foal and filly fair.

02:28.415 --> 02:29.882
<i>(sobbing)</i>

02:29.884 --> 02:32.384
I suppose I could.

02:32.386 --> 02:34.286
Forget it, spike.

02:34.288 --> 02:36.488
I'd never have something
finished in time.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.558
<i>(crying)</i>

02:43.796 --> 02:46.498
I wanted to leave my
creative mark on the fair

02:46.500 --> 02:48.267
And I have failed.

02:48.269 --> 02:49.601
Mmm.

02:49.603 --> 02:51.403
Miserably.

02:51.405 --> 02:55.674
And that makes me miserable.

02:55.676 --> 02:58.710
<i>(crying)</i>

03:05.852 --> 03:08.620
There's gotta be something
in here somewhere.

03:08.622 --> 03:09.922
Hoo!

03:09.924 --> 03:12.324
It's not who, it's what.

03:12.326 --> 03:15.727
Like what can help rarity make
something in time for the fair?

03:15.729 --> 03:19.364
She really, really, really wants
to make a creative contribution.

03:19.366 --> 03:21.433
She said I'm her
favourite dragon.

03:21.435 --> 03:24.736
So it's up to me to come through
for her in her time of need.

03:26.940 --> 03:29.608
There's gotta be some kind of
spell that'll do the trick.

03:29.610 --> 03:30.943
<i>Owl: Hoo!</i>

03:30.945 --> 03:32.778
Come on, help a dragon out!

03:34.214 --> 03:35.280
Hoo!

03:36.883 --> 03:37.950
Hoo!

03:40.720 --> 03:41.787
Hoo!

03:41.789 --> 03:42.788
Agh!

03:42.790 --> 03:43.956
It's not for me!

03:43.958 --> 03:47.659
The one who made you that
bow tie you liked so much.

03:47.661 --> 03:48.860
Hoo hoo!

03:48.862 --> 03:50.896
Ok. I get it.

03:52.632 --> 03:53.865
<i>(rumbling)</i>

03:53.867 --> 03:55.534
You don't think we
should use magi--

03:55.536 --> 04:01.306
♪

04:01.308 --> 04:03.609
What is that?

04:03.611 --> 04:05.010
Hoo! Hoo!

04:07.747 --> 04:08.914
<i>(whoosh)</i>

04:08.916 --> 04:10.382
<i>(clink)</i>

04:11.351 --> 04:13.819
Hoo! Hoo!

04:17.657 --> 04:20.459
<i>(squeaking bats)</i>

04:20.461 --> 04:27.532
♪

04:27.900 --> 04:30.502
Hoo! Hoo!

04:30.504 --> 04:34.640
If I wasn't supposed to have it,
it wouldn't be so easy to get.

04:34.642 --> 04:37.342
And it's covered
in spikes, like me!

04:37.344 --> 04:38.677
Hoooo!

04:38.679 --> 04:41.280
<i>(crashing)</i>

04:41.282 --> 04:42.648
Hooo!

04:42.650 --> 04:45.050
<i>(cracking)</i>

04:45.052 --> 04:50.622
"inspiration manifestation,
instantly brings ideas to life."

04:50.624 --> 04:52.758
I'm liking the
looks of this one!

04:52.760 --> 04:53.892
Hmm.

04:55.695 --> 04:56.795
<i>(slam)</i>

04:59.632 --> 05:01.700
<i>(rarity bawling)</i>

05:07.840 --> 05:09.074
Rarity!

05:09.076 --> 05:11.076
Leave me be!

05:11.078 --> 05:13.045
Can't you see how
distraught, disappointed

05:13.047 --> 05:16.481
And downtrodden I still am?

05:16.483 --> 05:18.950
But I brought you something.

05:18.952 --> 05:22.354
Unless it's another carton
of vanilla oat swirl

05:22.356 --> 05:24.856
Or word that the festival
has been cancelled,

05:24.858 --> 05:27.659
I don't think I'm interested.

05:27.661 --> 05:29.895
It's magic.

05:29.897 --> 05:33.565
Spike, precious scales,
I already have magic.

05:35.735 --> 05:37.936
But not the kind that can
help you create something

05:37.938 --> 05:40.072
In time for the fair.

05:40.074 --> 05:43.008
This can!

05:43.010 --> 05:45.610
I suppose it's worth a try.

05:45.612 --> 05:48.347
From in the head to
out in the world.

05:48.349 --> 05:50.716
Every thought to action.

05:50.718 --> 05:53.618
Hold close this book,
and through its spell,

05:53.620 --> 05:56.355
You'll start a chain reaction.

05:56.357 --> 05:59.591
Projecting forth
whatever beauty you see.

05:59.593 --> 06:05.130
Only when true words are spoken,
will you finally be set free.

06:05.132 --> 06:06.498
Did it work?

06:07.100 --> 06:08.867
There's only one
way to find out.

06:13.139 --> 06:14.473
<i>(poof)</i>

06:14.475 --> 06:16.108
Oh my!

06:16.110 --> 06:19.077
I thought about making this a
much more beautiful spell book

06:19.079 --> 06:20.545
And I have!

06:22.648 --> 06:23.782
<i>(poof)</i>

06:25.585 --> 06:28.920
Dear, dear, spike, here
I was about to give up,

06:28.922 --> 06:32.824
But like a true friend, you've
come through with flying colors.

06:34.594 --> 06:36.962
Come! We must find the
puppeteer right away

06:36.964 --> 06:39.631
So that I may provide him with
the most fabulous theatre

06:39.633 --> 06:41.600
He's ever imagined.

06:41.602 --> 06:46.471
Or should I say that
<u>I've</u> ever imagined.

06:56.916 --> 07:00.018
Ah, miss rarity, come to
see the show, I presume.

07:02.555 --> 07:05.090
You'll notice I had to make
do in light of your recent

07:05.092 --> 07:07.893
Failure to produce a
functioning theatre.

07:07.895 --> 07:13.498
♪

07:13.500 --> 07:16.001
Oh, but I think you'll find
the new one I've created

07:16.003 --> 07:18.503
Will be much more
to your liking.

07:21.507 --> 07:24.509
♪

07:24.511 --> 07:27.646
Hmm yeah well, it is gorgeous,

07:27.648 --> 07:29.781
But that was never the
problem now, was it?

07:31.083 --> 07:34.686
Oh, well this one
does seem to travel.

07:37.990 --> 07:41.059
Plenty of room for my puppets.

07:41.061 --> 07:43.962
I say, miss rarity, I don't
know how you managed to do so

07:43.964 --> 07:45.730
In such a short amount of time,

07:45.732 --> 07:49.100
But you seem to have
redeemed yourself.

07:49.102 --> 07:52.671
How did you manage to do
so in such a short time?

07:53.706 --> 07:55.707
As a matter of fact,
she used a sp-

07:55.709 --> 07:57.476
A good designer never
reveals her tricks.

08:01.147 --> 08:04.649
♪

08:04.651 --> 08:07.586
Thank you again, spike, for
being such a dear friend

08:07.588 --> 08:09.721
And finding this book for me.

08:09.723 --> 08:11.556
My pleasure.

08:11.558 --> 08:14.059
Well, guess I can return it
now that the fair is over.

08:14.061 --> 08:17.929
I've made my creative
contribution as I'd hoped to do,

08:17.931 --> 08:19.064
And all is well.

08:24.237 --> 08:28.206
Then again, perhaps I should
keep it just a skotch longer.

08:28.208 --> 08:29.975
You don't mind do you, spike?

08:30.643 --> 08:32.511
Of course not!

08:32.513 --> 08:33.912
See you tomorrow.

08:37.617 --> 08:38.750
What?

08:38.752 --> 08:40.552
She'll keep it for
a few more hours.

08:40.554 --> 08:41.620
No harm in that.

08:44.991 --> 08:49.561
<i>(spike whistling cheerfully)</i>

08:49.563 --> 08:51.229
<i>(knock knock knock)</i>

08:51.231 --> 08:52.264
Rarity?

08:52.266 --> 08:55.800
<i>(rumbling)</i>

08:55.802 --> 08:56.868
Wha!

08:57.937 --> 08:59.838
Spike! I'm so glad
you're here!

09:04.844 --> 09:06.077
Whoa!

09:09.815 --> 09:11.850
Are you ok?

09:11.852 --> 09:13.552
Oh! I've never been better.

09:13.554 --> 09:15.687
This book you've
given me is amazing!

09:15.689 --> 09:18.290
Why, I've been up all night
just creating and creating

09:18.292 --> 09:20.125
And creating and creating!

09:20.127 --> 09:24.062
I've completed my fall line
for the next fifteen seasons!

09:24.064 --> 09:25.330
Wow!

09:25.332 --> 09:28.099
But then I started
thinking, why stop there?

09:28.101 --> 09:30.602
Oh, spike, I've always
thought this town of ours

09:30.604 --> 09:32.704
Could use a few
beautifying upgrades.

09:32.706 --> 09:36.207
And with this book, I can make
that happen with such ease.

09:36.209 --> 09:38.577
You will support me in this
endeavor by letting me

09:38.579 --> 09:40.779
Keep the book just
a little longer?

09:41.581 --> 09:43.014
Of course I will!

09:44.884 --> 09:46.851
Hoo!

09:52.291 --> 09:55.193
What do you say we get a little
breakfast before we get started?

09:55.195 --> 09:56.595
No time for breakfast.

09:56.597 --> 09:58.363
I want to get
started right away.

09:58.365 --> 10:00.298
Technically, we do have time

10:00.300 --> 10:01.933
Because with that
book held close

10:01.935 --> 10:03.101
You can just
make things--

10:05.338 --> 10:06.605
Rarity?

10:09.308 --> 10:13.044
Now this is exactly
what I'm talking about.

10:13.046 --> 10:15.380
Why that cart hasn't an
ounce of stylish flair.

10:19.685 --> 10:20.819
<i>(poof)</i>

10:24.357 --> 10:27.759
My eyes playin'
tricks on me again?

10:27.761 --> 10:29.794
What in rhubarb
pie just happened?

10:32.098 --> 10:33.965
Isn't it gorgeous?

10:33.967 --> 10:35.166
It's amazing!

10:35.168 --> 10:36.968
You should ask applejack
if she wants you

10:36.970 --> 10:39.170
To give all the apple
family carts a makeover!

10:39.172 --> 10:42.841
Oh, I don't really think I need
to ask permission, darling.

10:42.843 --> 10:44.943
Everyone loves surprises.

10:44.945 --> 10:47.312
Especially when they're
gorgeous ones.

10:47.314 --> 10:48.313
You're right!

10:48.315 --> 10:50.315
Everypony does love surprises!

10:50.317 --> 10:53.752
We shouldn't even tell
anypony that it's me

10:53.754 --> 10:56.421
Who is behind all the fabulous
changes I'll be making.

10:56.423 --> 10:57.689
<i>(giggle)</i>

10:57.691 --> 10:59.124
Won't that be a
fun little secret

10:59.126 --> 11:00.992
For the three of
us to share?

11:00.994 --> 11:03.728
The... Three of us?

11:05.164 --> 11:07.832
You, me, and the
book, of course.

11:10.202 --> 11:13.071
My marvellous,
marvellous book.

11:14.807 --> 11:16.241
Of course.

11:16.243 --> 11:18.910
Promise me you won't
say a word to anypony?

11:20.346 --> 11:21.846
You got it!

11:21.848 --> 11:24.082
I knew I could
count on you, spike.

11:24.084 --> 11:26.685
And I also know just
what I want to do next.

11:27.953 --> 11:30.121
Take that!

11:30.123 --> 11:31.189
And that!

11:32.925 --> 11:33.925
Ha ha.

11:33.927 --> 11:34.926
<i>(poof)</i>

11:34.928 --> 11:35.994
What in the--

11:35.996 --> 11:40.331
Get. It. Off. Of. Me!

11:40.333 --> 11:42.167
I've always thought
rainbow dash

11:42.169 --> 11:44.135
Could use a little more glamour.

11:44.137 --> 11:45.236
And now look at her!

11:45.238 --> 11:47.138
Cloud-busting with style!

11:48.774 --> 11:49.841
Moving on!

11:51.377 --> 11:52.410
She'll be fine.

11:52.412 --> 11:54.045
It's just a dress.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.980
Wait for your favorite dragon!

11:57.917 --> 11:59.017
<i>(crash)</i>

11:59.019 --> 12:00.385
<i>(sigh)</i>

12:04.957 --> 12:08.093
<i>♪ la la la la la la</i>

12:08.095 --> 12:09.994
There you go, mr. Robin.

12:09.996 --> 12:11.396
<i>(chirping)</i>

12:13.065 --> 12:15.300
Don't you look so content
in your little house.

12:15.302 --> 12:16.735
<i>(poof)</i>

12:16.737 --> 12:18.069
Oh my goodness!

12:19.839 --> 12:20.872
You're lost?

12:20.874 --> 12:22.107
<i>(chirp)</i>

12:22.109 --> 12:23.341
No. Not that way.

12:23.343 --> 12:26.144
That looks like that's
a door to a bedroom.

12:26.146 --> 12:27.245
Try that one over there.

12:27.247 --> 12:28.379
<i>(chirp)</i>

12:28.381 --> 12:29.380
No. No.

12:29.382 --> 12:31.349
That leads to a...

12:31.351 --> 12:32.517
Shoe closet?

12:32.519 --> 12:33.752
Oh dear.

12:33.754 --> 12:35.253
Maybe try the staircase?

12:35.255 --> 12:38.056
No. No. No. The
other staircase.

12:38.058 --> 12:39.858
Isn't it gorgeous?

12:39.860 --> 12:42.927
It's probably the most beautiful
bird house ever created...

12:42.929 --> 12:46.898
I'm just not sure how
the bird feels about it.

12:46.900 --> 12:51.369
Pfft. What does a bird know
about architectural design?

12:51.371 --> 12:54.939
What matters is what you
think, spike, and you love it.

12:54.941 --> 12:57.242
Don't you?

12:57.244 --> 12:58.376
Of course I do!

12:58.378 --> 13:02.147
It's so... "rarity".

13:02.149 --> 13:03.381
It is, isn't it.

13:04.550 --> 13:05.817
Oooh!

13:07.086 --> 13:08.153
<i>(clunk)</i>

13:14.026 --> 13:20.265
<i>(kids chattering)</i>

13:20.267 --> 13:22.834
Oh, adorable!

13:22.836 --> 13:25.937
But it could use a touch
of class, don't you think?

13:25.939 --> 13:27.972
Oh. Yeah. Definitely!

13:27.974 --> 13:32.010
<i>♪ (country swing)</i>

13:32.012 --> 13:33.244
<i>(poof)</i>

13:35.381 --> 13:36.881
<i>(poof)</i>

13:41.287 --> 13:43.588
This party doesn't even
seem to have a proper theme.

13:43.590 --> 13:46.825
Let's do something
about that, shall we?

13:46.827 --> 13:49.327
You've already made things
look really, really great.

13:49.329 --> 13:51.963
Maybe you should stop
while you're ahead?

13:51.965 --> 13:53.398
You're right, spike.

13:53.400 --> 13:55.834
There's so much
to do elsewhere.

13:55.836 --> 13:57.101
Right.

13:57.103 --> 13:58.369
Elsewhere.

13:58.371 --> 14:00.405
Just one more little
thing before we go.

14:01.574 --> 14:02.607
<i>(poof)</i>

14:02.609 --> 14:04.509
<i>♪ (classical)</i>

14:04.511 --> 14:08.446
Why, this party is certain
to make the society page now.

14:08.448 --> 14:12.217
Won't pinkie pie be pleased?

14:12.219 --> 14:15.019
Happy happy day to--huh?

14:19.258 --> 14:21.459
I am simply buzzing with ideas.

14:21.461 --> 14:22.527
Simply buzzing!

14:24.497 --> 14:28.466
But, uh, you've been at
this for a while now.

14:28.468 --> 14:30.068
How about you take a break?

14:30.070 --> 14:32.170
Give that brilliant
mind of yours a rest.

14:32.172 --> 14:33.471
<i>Don't be silly.</i>

14:33.473 --> 14:35.473
I'm not going to stop now.

14:35.475 --> 14:38.142
Why, I won't stop until
every inch of ponyville

14:38.144 --> 14:40.144
Has benefited from
my creative vision.

14:43.649 --> 14:45.416
Starting with you, spike!

14:51.991 --> 14:52.991
You.

14:52.993 --> 14:53.992
Look.

14:53.994 --> 14:55.426
Fabulous!

14:55.428 --> 14:57.462
All because of you!

14:57.464 --> 15:02.133
Anything for my favorite dragon
and most supportive friend.

15:02.135 --> 15:04.335
Come! There's so
much more to do!

15:07.673 --> 15:09.440
Oh, no!

15:09.442 --> 15:10.575
Not you, too.

15:12.678 --> 15:15.280
What do you mean "not me, too"?

15:15.282 --> 15:18.182
Oh, judging by that outfit, I
thought for sure you'd--

15:18.184 --> 15:19.284
What? This?

15:19.286 --> 15:21.286
I just wanted to
try out a new look.

15:21.288 --> 15:22.553
<i>(thud)</i>

15:22.555 --> 15:24.255
You like?

15:24.257 --> 15:29.327
Well, in that case, have you
seen anypony suspicious around?

15:29.329 --> 15:30.595
Uh, nope.

15:35.035 --> 15:38.202
The gazebo has been
turned into solid crystal

15:38.204 --> 15:40.705
And two ponies are now
trapped inside its walls!

15:47.347 --> 15:52.350
No! I made a promise to rarity
to keep this to myself.

15:52.352 --> 15:53.351
Hoo!

15:53.353 --> 15:57.655
But you're right
owlowiscious, I have to tell.

15:57.657 --> 16:00.959
And once I do, I can forget
rarity thinking of me

16:00.961 --> 16:03.561
As her most supportive friend.

16:03.563 --> 16:07.432
I can forget rarity thinking
of me as a friend at all.

16:17.509 --> 16:19.377
I can't do it.

16:20.179 --> 16:23.147
I promised I'd keep all of
this between the three of us.

16:23.149 --> 16:24.582
Hoo!

16:24.584 --> 16:26.751
Of course, it's weird
that she meant me, her,

16:26.753 --> 16:28.753
And the spell book, but--

16:28.755 --> 16:31.022
The spell book! Of course!

16:31.024 --> 16:32.690
If I can get it away from her,

16:32.692 --> 16:35.059
I bet she won't be able
to use its magic anymore.

16:36.662 --> 16:38.997
<i>Oh, come on! It's</i>
<i>the perfect plan.</i>

16:38.999 --> 16:41.766
I just have to figure
out which way she went.

16:41.768 --> 16:43.401
<i>I can't see!</i>

16:43.403 --> 16:48.539
<i>(screams)</i>

16:48.541 --> 16:51.409
I'm thinking she's
headed this way.

16:54.179 --> 16:55.580
<i>(evil cackle)</i>

17:08.227 --> 17:09.694
What do you think
you're doing?

17:09.696 --> 17:14.632
Me? I was just uh, basking
in your creative radiance.

17:16.268 --> 17:19.637
Oh, spike, you do say
the nicest things!

17:19.639 --> 17:21.539
Thanks.

17:21.541 --> 17:23.341
Now where was I?

17:27.247 --> 17:31.649
Gold-plated roof-tops
for everypony!

17:31.651 --> 17:33.718
Hoo! Hoo! Hoo!

17:39.792 --> 17:41.059
Spike!

17:42.061 --> 17:43.194
<i>(munch)</i>

17:44.530 --> 17:46.564
I have just had the
most marvellous idea!

17:47.199 --> 17:49.200
<i>(gulp)</i>

17:49.202 --> 17:50.435
<i>(sigh)</i>

17:50.437 --> 17:52.837
Of course you have;
you're rarity.

17:54.273 --> 17:56.841
My work here in ponyville
is nearly complete.

17:56.843 --> 17:59.610
Don't you think it's time
the rest of equestria

17:59.612 --> 18:01.546
Benefited from my
creative vision?

18:02.448 --> 18:03.614
Absolutely!

18:04.817 --> 18:07.585
I'm thinking we go by chariot.

18:07.587 --> 18:10.621
Or as everyone will soon
be calling them, "rariot".

18:10.623 --> 18:12.723
<i>(manic giggle)</i>

18:12.725 --> 18:15.159
Oh, yeah! We should
definitely go by--

18:15.161 --> 18:16.360
<i>(poof)</i>

18:19.665 --> 18:23.101
How...How did you do that?

18:23.103 --> 18:25.169
Why, whatever do you mean?

18:25.171 --> 18:28.306
The book. It's... I
mean... You don't...

18:28.308 --> 18:29.874
It's gone.

18:29.876 --> 18:31.275
The book is gone.

18:31.277 --> 18:32.310
Gone?

18:32.312 --> 18:33.611
Why it's right there.

18:33.613 --> 18:35.213
<i>(gasp)</i>

18:35.215 --> 18:37.181
I need my book, spike!

18:37.183 --> 18:38.816
What have you done
with my book?

18:38.818 --> 18:40.485
<i>(growl)</i>

18:40.487 --> 18:42.820
Why would I do anything
with your book?

18:42.822 --> 18:44.288
We're friends.

18:44.290 --> 18:46.424
It was probably the owl!

18:47.827 --> 18:53.831
But, wait, I don't seem
to need it anymore, do I?

18:53.833 --> 18:56.434
Yes! Yes!

18:56.436 --> 18:59.604
I can feel its magic
flowing within me now.

18:59.606 --> 19:03.241
I'm so excited!
I'm so excited!

19:03.243 --> 19:04.876
I'm so scared.

19:04.878 --> 19:06.711
<i>Oh, the places</i>
<i>we'll go, spike.</i>

19:06.713 --> 19:07.778
Manehattan.

19:07.780 --> 19:08.880
Phillydelphia.

19:08.882 --> 19:10.548
Canterlot.

19:10.550 --> 19:12.350
And there you'll
be by my side.

19:12.352 --> 19:14.418
Just as you've always
been here in ponyville.

19:14.420 --> 19:16.821
Your constant praise and
adoration driving me

19:16.823 --> 19:18.489
To even greater heights

19:18.491 --> 19:19.924
Until there isn't an
inch of equestria

19:19.926 --> 19:21.792
That hasn't been
utterly transformed

19:21.794 --> 19:25.530
By my creative genius!

19:25.532 --> 19:31.569
♪

19:31.571 --> 19:32.937
No!

19:32.939 --> 19:34.872
What did you say?

19:34.874 --> 19:36.541
I said, "no!"

19:36.543 --> 19:37.742
You've been changing things,

19:37.744 --> 19:39.710
But you haven't been
making them better.

19:39.712 --> 19:42.280
I should have told you the
truth at the very beginning,

19:42.282 --> 19:45.583
Because I was trying to be
a supportive friend.

19:45.585 --> 19:49.854
But instead I let you
become something awful.

19:51.290 --> 19:52.356
Awful?

20:02.568 --> 20:05.570
What happened?

20:05.572 --> 20:08.239
Rarity, you're ok?

20:08.241 --> 20:11.642
I...I think so.

20:11.644 --> 20:14.545
Though by the looks of it,
something quite terrifying

20:14.547 --> 20:16.447
Has happened to ponyville.

20:17.616 --> 20:19.217
You happened.

20:19.219 --> 20:20.318
Me?

20:21.453 --> 20:24.288
The last part of the spell!

20:24.290 --> 20:26.524
"only when true
words are spoken,

20:26.526 --> 20:29.327
Will you finally be set free."

20:30.329 --> 20:31.996
The spell took over you

20:31.998 --> 20:34.532
And you wanted to change
everything in equestria.

20:34.534 --> 20:37.602
I was afraid to tell you
how I really felt about it,

20:37.604 --> 20:40.938
But then I, I told
you the truth.

20:40.940 --> 20:45.243
Dearest spike, you should never
be afraid to tell me the truth.

20:45.245 --> 20:46.777
We're friends, remember?

20:50.482 --> 20:52.383
<i>Spike: Today I learned</i>
<i>how important it is</i>

20:52.385 --> 20:53.818
<i>To be honest with your friends</i>

20:53.820 --> 20:54.986
<i>When they're doing something</i>

20:54.988 --> 20:56.787
<i>That you don't think is right.</i>

20:56.789 --> 20:59.023
A true friend knows
that you're speaking up

20:59.025 --> 21:00.491
Because you care about them.

21:00.493 --> 21:01.492
<i>(door opens)</i>

21:01.494 --> 21:06.998
Never, ever, ever take another
book out of the library

21:07.000 --> 21:09.500
At the castle without asking.

21:09.502 --> 21:11.002
Princess cadance
and princess luna

21:11.004 --> 21:13.904
Have much better things to do
than help me clean up ponyville.

21:16.475 --> 21:18.809
Do you have any idea how
hard it was to reverse

21:18.811 --> 21:19.944
That much dark magic?

21:21.847 --> 21:23.281
You don't look so good.

21:24.750 --> 21:25.750
What?

21:25.752 --> 21:26.917
I'm just being honest.

21:26.919 --> 21:28.519
It's what good friends do.

21:29.688 --> 21:32.290
(growl)

21:33.558 --> 21:35.926
♪ my little pony

21:37.896 --> 21:40.464
♪ my little pony

21:50.809 --> 21:52.877
♪ my little pony

21:52.944 --> 21:57.014
♪ friends
